  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. Factor the numerator: x\u00b2 + 4x \u2212 12 = (x + 6)(x \u2212 2). The equation becomes (x + 6)(x \u2212 2)/(x + 6) = x \u2212 2 (for x \u2260 \u22126). So p = 1 and q = \u22122, giving p + q = \u22121.</p><p>Choice A is the value of p alone. Choice C is the value of q alone. Choice B is incorrect from a sign error.</p>",
